  "why": "The paper's TESTRNN framework explicitly steers test generation toward predefined internal test-conditions (BC, SC, TC) using a targeted (genetic) mutation guided by fitness functions that minimize distance to those conditions. The evaluation demonstrates that this guidance discovers security-relevant classes of failures — notably adversarial examples and backdoor-triggering inputs — but the method is driven to satisfy internal coverage conditions (patterns of activations/temporal behaviors) and to find any misclassification/backdoor behavior, not to force the model to produce a specific attacker-chosen target output/label. Thus it targets broader classes of security-violating behavior (adversarial/backdoor) rather than specific attacker-selected outputs.",
